children.subject: I can't answer for Stat 155, but CS 161 and CS 168 is a fair but definitely doable workload when combined. Plus both are awesome classes!

What year are you? If this is your first semester of upper divs, it might be a bit tougher than average, but I think those are a good combo of CS courses. I'm also not sure about STAT155, but in general 3 techs is doable given a reasonable amount of extracurriculars. I might recommend only 2 techs you first time with UD courses, especially if you have a lot of outside commitments.

Your year will make the biggest difference in getting in. It's hard to say, but if you are able to phase 1 these courses, I'd be shocked in you didn't get into 1, and would expect 2 of 3 wouldn't be unreasonable, especially if you want to wait out the waiting list.

history.content:
For Fall 2017, I'm hoping to take the above classes (plus a seminar and likely something else that's 1/2 units). To anyone who's taken any of these classes, how were they + is this a manageable schedule? Also, I know they're all fairly popular classes - what are my chances of getting all of them? 

Thanks :)
history.subject: CS 161, CS 168, STAT 155
